caption: Absolutely Love Love Love! The Super Mansion!! Guys!! Trust Me, I eat out alot, and this is my favorite Super go to Gem!!! There covid protocol is spot on! Everyone is actually wearing there mask, over there noses, Which I love! Big shout out, to there beautiful, friendly Employees! Omg, and of course the chef, is amazing! Order the Skirt Steak!!!!!! That steak keeps me coming back for more! There's outside and indoor dining. The outside is actually heated, so you can book a table all year round. I love the outside! They did such a good job, setting up the outdoor, it's so spacious, cute, comfy and fun! Thers a DJ, playing all the best hits, keeping you dancing,from the minute you walk in, and you can't help dancing in ur seat, the whole time. The Restrooms are spotless, and it's actually so pretty down stairs, that you have to pull out ur phone and take pics. Lol For my daughters birthday, the employees came out with a cake, big super mansion birthday sign, and those big firery candles, singing and dancing happy birthday to her. I was not expecting that, and it was so cute and fun! So THANK YOU! To everyone at the Super Mansion, for all the love and care you show ur customers, and making my baby's 13 teenth birthday, one she will always remember. 🤗😚
Friendly staff! Great atmosphere!
I did my 30th this past Saturday and I must say the place  was very nice . The owner made sure my guest was happy and I had an amazing experience ! The music was great and the  food . Thank you !

Went there for a birthday celebration. We were offered the prix fix menu. I ordered the ceviche which was amazing. My main course was the mar y tierra. My skirt steak was cooked perfectly to my liking with shrimp which wasn't over done and potatoes. My third course was the panna cotta which was delicious. The experience was amazing. We went over to the lounge area were we continued drinking until closing. I will definitely go back there real soon.
Nice service and delicious ceviche, high price points.

Service was NOT the greatest.  I guess that's why they automatically add a 20 percent gratitude to your bill. The food was ok.  It was my first time there.  Perhaps the staff was having an off day.  I'll probably visit again and see how the second visit goes.
It was good

I visited Mansion Supper Club for a Ron Viejo de Caldas event. Everything was incredible: the food, ambience, entertainment, and service. It is very large and has different areas, some for eat, bar, lounge. Very nice!

This place is great! Atmosphere is welcoming, charming, hospitable hosts, delicious dishes, beautiful presentation,  The staff is also really friendly. We are so fortunate to have this place in Astoria.  Stunning dining room and cozy lounge, great for cocktails and sharing good times. Love this place and will continue to visit.
Great food and drinks. Staff is also very friendly and accommodating. Love coming here!

Only amazing things can be said. For starters, the service was one of the best. Staff is so kind and welcoming. Now the food is AMAZING!!! The flavors and plating definitely is worth the visit. I went with my husband and friends of ours at night to celebrate a birthday and let me tell you the drinks and music were hands down one of the best!
Great food and Latin music!!!!
Amazing food! Excellent service
Great ambiance !
Great place for reopening to nyc indoor dinning.

From the moment you walk in your know this restaurant is special , from the bar to the dining room it's beautiful . Then the great service brings out such great food and drinks . I can't wait to go back .

Been here plenty of times and it's always  great vibes,great times! Their food and drinks are delicious and well-priced. I definitely recommend checking this place out!

We went for sunday brunch here, food was terrible, and expensive. First time ive had waffles deep fried in oil, ended up spending over 300 dollars and normally i do not mind paying for food and entertainment, but this was not a good experience.

It is not a place for you to eat just to drink, the snacks are horrible, the place is beautiful with good music, the service is good.  Only the food that is bad, I tried some options but nothing came tasty, and the presentation doesn’t help either, it’s a Latin place.guacamole came with practically whole avocado.  horrible.
Everything was so good,  the food, the cocktails and the attention.  Nice place.
This establishment opened one month before the Pandemic. Their adaptation  to provide exceptional service with there new outdoor seating was impressive. A definite  high recommendation

The Garden delivers on its promise. It surely is a transporting experience. Felt like a restaurant on a Caribbean island. Service was spot on. Beers were cold and the food surpassed our expectations. The crab cakes were excellent. I subbed a salad for the yucca fries and it was dressed perfectly in what seemed like a semi sweet mango dressing, not drenched.  The cakes were served atop a tasty aoili, again flavorful and perfectly cooked. Kids had fish and chicken tacos. Left nothing behind. (And we fancy ourselves taco connoisseurs lol) Will be back! Oh, Almost forgot, felt super safe with the plexi partitions between tables!
Service wasn't good food wasnt that great either
If you’re looking for a great day/night with family  or friends, Mansion’s the place to go. The food and drinks are delicious, and the service’s outstanding. It’s a must! 👍🏽👍🏽
Excellent.

I went there for my birthday with a group of 9 people. My party arrived before me and they would  let them in and wait even thou we made reservations. i requeated a table by the straw wall when i made the reservation  but they still didnt give me one  even thou there was a empty one. the  atmosphere is great But i will not return. The drinks are great however the service and food is terriable Lobster roll and all the other food were super tiny and flavor less but overpriced.  there hookah was terrible.We had bought  in a cake. Our bill was over 800$ but they tried to charge us 50$ for paper plates  provide to serve our cake. Ive never heard of that in my life. Also wish they would let you mix  the bottle service package,  where u should be able to get a champagne and liquore but its either or. Over the only  think nice about this place is decor. I had high expectations

Great new place with a beautiful outside dining experience, price very comfortable and food is delightful. The atmosphere was very pleasant and our server Carolina was extremely attentive. What a nice place to go during this pandemic times. I would definitely recommend this place and i am going to return soon enough.
Great spot for a date or to go with your friends friendly staff despite covid conditions this place has a lot of space and prices are reasonable.
Ambiance feels like I slipped into miami for lunch/dinner. It is so cute!! Food was eh. But I did love the guac. Drinks were good! So if i come back it will be only for the drinks...

Outdoor patio is nice. Otherwise, this place was a real let-down. Ask for waters & they’ll bring you bottles at $4 a pop. Lobster & Mansion Sandwich both beyond subpar. $10 of guac gets you a Chipotle size scoop.

Cute place but beware.  Their Instagram states "Happy hour daily ". However,  when I went on a Saturday,  the waitress informed me that its only Monday through Friday. Whoever does their Marketing on IG should really fix that. Its deceiving.

Horrible service, went to eat there for my anniversary... or so I thought. Security person didn't even really pay attention to us and he said that the garden was reserved for large groups of 5 or more. It was only 2 of us. We got seated on the outside of the restaurant (by the front door) and waited for 25min for the server. She never even came. We left after we saw that she started waiting on a group of 3 people that came right after us and got seated right away. Poor service, managerial, customer and just horrible experience overall. Never again. Horrible, horrible, horrible.

Really like this place, the new outside setting "the garden" is perfect for the summer time; fun ambiance and music, the lobter roll is really good!  Went with friends and we had a great time... happy to be able to be outside again.. exactly what I needed.  Also, given the currect circustances I'm happy to see they are taking all the necessary steps to keep everyone safe. Will be going again soon!
Excellent lobster rolls really recommend going it is so good reasonable prices i love ❤️ .Amazing sliders .Burgers are out of this world.
After being in quarantine for 3 months it was so nice to be outside. Went out on a date with my husband. The food is great, definitely worth it. Beautiful sunset ...

Only one star cuz I can’t rate less. $11 drink for a cup full of ice and watered down alcohol. Sat outside cuz I didn’t have a RSVP and didn’t want to walk in for a $250 table. Idk who these people think they are, def not worth the price.  If you still wanna go, rsvp online for free admission. Place looks nice ngl. Music good. Good sunset pic. But needs to improve drinks and service.

Mansion Supper Club is new Latin restaurant/club worth checking out.  Multiple dining and lounging rooms each offering a different and special ambiance with an amazing  bar as you enter the restaurant. Some of the tasty dishes we enjoyed were the organic herb roasted chicken which was  moist and cooked to perfection, delicious baked plantains, baked branzino fish with sautéed radishes and herbs with potatoes and a tender filet mignon.
Such a great New year’s eve, the food the out of this world, the music was popping. This place is a gem!
Delicious food, amazing drinks, great DJ!
